properties.Name: EquifaxCompanyAverageDaysBeyondTerms
properties.Description: Displays the dollar-weighted average days beyond terms on nonfinancial accounts within the last 12 months from the date of the inquiry; calculated from dollar amounts reported for aging categories 1-5; if no information was reported for a given month within the 12-month period, no line will appear in the graph for that month.

Columns.Name: EfxId
Columns.Description: The EFX ID™ is a unique and persistent nine-digit number that identifies and tracks the business unit with which you have the credit relationship;

Columns.Name: ProfileTimestamp
Columns.Description:
Provides the timestamp when the inquiry was made as recorded
by Equifax (Eastern Time).

Columns.Name: AverageDaysBeyondTermsDateReported
Columns.Description: The as-of date for which the average days beyond terms is based.

Columns.Name: AverageDaysBeyondTerms
Columns.Description: The average number of days beyond the specified terms that the company makes payments.
